  "aboutText": "Alocasia azlanii is a stunning, compact terrestrial herb native to the lowland and montane rainforests of Sabah, Malaysian Borneo. Highly prized by collectors for its dark, metallic-green to maroon leaves, it is famously distinguished by its vivid, iridescent pink to red venation. The plant grows from a distinct basal corm, maintaining a neat basal rosette habit that remains smaller and more bullate than its relative, Alocasia reginula. Thriving in humid, shaded conditions, this species requires well-drained, humus-rich soil to mimic its natural forest-floor habitat.",
